{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today we celebrate the stunning Spanish islands of the Balearic archipelago. This diverse and deeply Mediterranean territory includes Mallorca, Menorca, Ibiza and Formentera, each shaped by centuries of history and a close relationship with the sea.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BalearesDay_ROW4071522082_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BalearesDay_ROW4071522082_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Ibiza, Balearic Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© tokar/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260301_BalearesDay\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Ibiza+city&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260301_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260301_BalearesDay"},"Ssd":"20260301","Name":"BalearesDay","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4071522082","FullDateString":"1. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Moloka'i, often called the most Hawaiian of the islands, offers a slower rhythm shaped by nature and strong community ties. Formed by volcanic activity more than a million years ago, the island covers about 670 square kilometres and rises from the Pacific Ocean in long ridges and broad valleys. Unlike its busier neighbours, Moloka'i has resisted large-scale development, preserving a strong sense of local cohesion where families, traditions and stewardship of the land encapsulate central values. Life here focuses on the ocean, the land and stories passed down through generations.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OloupenaFalls_ROW3892366742_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OloupenaFalls_ROW3892366742_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Olo'upena Falls, island of Moloka'i, Hawaii, United States","Copyright":"© Andrew Aylett/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260228_OloupenaFalls\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Molokai&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260228_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260228_OloupenaFalls"},"Ssd":"20260228","Name":"OloupenaFalls","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3892366742","FullDateString":"28. Feb rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Polar bears are closely tied to their frozen Arctic realms, roaming vast icy landscapes and sometimes covering hundreds of kilometres in search of food. The world's largest land carnivores are perfectly adapted to life on sea ice, with large paws that can span more than 30 centimetres and help them swim for kilometres.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArcitcCub_ROW3693461289_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArcitcCub_ROW3693461289_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Polar bear cub walking across pack ice, Arctic National Wildlife Refuge, Alaska, United States","Copyright":"© Steven Kazlowski/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260227_ArcitcCub\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Polar+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260227_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260227_ArcitcCub"},"Ssd":"20260227","Name":"ArcitcCub","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3693461289","FullDateString":"27. Feb rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every day at the Grand Canyon National Park in Arizona, United States, tells a story. At the heart of it all flows the Colorado River, winding for hundreds of kilometres through layered stone, quietly shaping the canyon one season at a time. Visitors can slow down and explore through ranger-led programs and talks that highlight the canyon's geology, wildlife and cultural history. A walk along the South Rim offers sweeping views where California condors circle overhead, while elk, mule deer and bighorn sheep roam the park's diverse habitats. Stargazing and scenic overlooks add to the experience, especially during winter's clearer nights.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrandSunset_ROW3515132743_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrandSunset_ROW3515132743_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grand Canyon and the Colorado River, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Matt Anderson Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260226_GrandSunset\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Canyon+National+Park+USA&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260226_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260226_GrandSunset"},"Ssd":"20260226","Name":"GrandSunset","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3515132743","FullDateString":"26. Feb rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Hidden just outside Juneau in Alaska, United States, the Mendenhall Glacier feels almost unreal, inside and out. Step into one of its rare blue ice caves, and the world turns quiet and luminous, with light filtering through centuries-old compacted ice. The glacier stretches about 21 kilometres from the Juneau Icefield, slowly flowing toward the valley below and reshaping itself year by year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MendenhallCave_ROW3350238488_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MendenhallCave_ROW3350238488_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Ice cave in the Mendenhall Glacier, Alaska, United States","Copyright":"© Designpics/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260225_MendenhallCave\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mendenhall+Glacier&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260225_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260225_MendenhallCave"},"Ssd":"20260225","Name":"MendenhallCave","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3350238488","FullDateString":"25. Feb rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Floating lilies, glass-clear pools and a hidden world below: welcome to the Grand Cenote in Tulum, Mexico. This natural sinkhole formed thousands of years ago when collapsing rock let aquifer waters in. Over time, the chamber filled with clear freshwater that now connects a vast underground system of caves. At first, our eyes rest on the still surface. The water lilies we see in the image float without hurry, their broad leaves catching sunlight while supporting rich ecosystems underneath. These botanical wonders belong to one of the oldest flowering lineages on Earth, dating back more than 125 million years—older than most dinosaurs. Each bloom has evolved clever tricks to attract pollinators—beetles, bees, flies and even the wind—using scent, shape and timing to ensure survival in still water.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TulumLilies_ROW3115035500_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TulumLilies_ROW3115035500_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Water lilies at Grand Cenote, Tulum, Mexico","Copyright":"© Christian Vizl/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260224_TulumLilies\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grand+Cenote+Tulum&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260224_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260224_TulumLilies"},"Ssd":"20260224","Name":"TulumLilies","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3115035500","FullDateString":"24. Feb rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The great egret is a striking large heron, easily recognisable by its pure white plumage, long neck and sharp yellow bill. Known for its cosmopolitan distribution, it occupies habitats around the world and adapts well to many aquatic environments. Adults measure about 94–104 centimetres in body length, with a wingspan of 1.3 to 1.5 metres and weigh about a kilogram, giving them a tall, elegant silhouette—roughly chest‑high when compared to a 2‑metre-tall person. As carnivores, they feed primarily on fish but also take amphibians, insects, small mammals and occasionally reptiles. Their patient hunting style, standing motionless before striking with sudden precision, is one of their most distinctive traits.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BavariaEgret_ROW2876151337_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BavariaEgret_ROW2876151337_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Great white egret, Upper Bavaria, Germany","Copyright":"© Konrad Wothe/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260223_BavariaEgret\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Great+white+egret&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260223_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260223_BavariaEgret"},"Ssd":"20260223","Name":"BavariaEgret","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2876151337","FullDateString":"23. Feb rrrr"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine reaching the Brocken in Harz National Park, Germany, as clouds slide across the ridge. With the sun behind you, mist ahead—then a giant, haloed shadow forms. Ever wondered why climbers once feared this sight? The phenomenon, called the Brocken spectre, is an eerie natural optical effect that occurs when sunlight projects a person's shadow onto cloud or fog. Rising about 1,141 metres, the Brocken is the highest peak in northern Germany and has long inspired folklore, including tales of witches gathering here during Walpurgis Night.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BrockenSunrise_ROW5181265545_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BrockenSunrise_ROW5181265545_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sunrise on the Brocken, Harz National Park, Germany","Copyright":"© imageBROKER/AVTG/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260308_BrockenSunrise\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Harz+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260308_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260308_BrockenSunrise"},"Ssd":"20260308","Name":"BrockenSunrise","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5181265545","FullDateString":"8. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Owls are full of contradictions. Silent wings, loud opinions. They are night hunters that somehow feel ancient. From myths to cartoons, they have always had a presence. Athena's owl symbolised wisdom, while pop culture gave us lines we still quote—remember Owl from 'Winnie-the-Pooh' always sounding sure of himself?","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OwlonGuard_ROW4856156035_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OwlonGuard_ROW4856156035_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Snowy owl near the Canadian Rockies, Canada","Copyright":"© www.harshadventure.com/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260307_OwlonGuard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Snowy+owl&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260307_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260307_OwlonGuard"},"Ssd":"20260307","Name":"OwlonGuard","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4856156035","FullDateString":"7. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Architecture blends art and technology, expressed through the built form. While many designs focus primarily on function, some buildings give equal weight to visual impact. A strong example is The Wave building complex in Vejle, Denmark, where sculptural design and practical housing come together seamlessly.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WaveDenmark_ROW5073761456_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WaveDenmark_ROW5073761456_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The Wave residential building, Vejle, Denmark","Copyright":"© Frank Bach/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260306_WaveDenmark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=The+Wave+building+Vejle+Denmark&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260306_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260306_WaveDenmark"},"Ssd":"20260306","Name":"WaveDenmark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5073761456","FullDateString":"6. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As evening settles over the town of Göreme in the heart of the Cappadocia region of Türkiye, dusk reveals a landscape forged by nature and centuries of human presence. This scene is part of Göreme National Park and the Rock Sites of Cappadocia, a UNESCO World Heritage Site inscribed in 1985 for its exceptional combination of early cultural history and geological formations. These formations, often called 'fairy chimneys' or hoodoos, began as layers of volcanic ash that hardened into soft stone following eruptions of ancient Anatolian volcanoes. Over time, wind and water carved the pillars, ridges and valleys that define the region today.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GoremeTwilight_ROW5000170185_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GoremeTwilight_ROW5000170185_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Göreme, Cappadocia, Türkiye","Copyright":"© ONNAJA/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260305_GoremeTwilight\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=G%c3%b6reme+T%c3%bcrkiye&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260305_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260305_GoremeTwilight"},"Ssd":"20260305","Name":"GoremeTwilight","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5000170185","FullDateString":"5. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As winter's grip on the Rila Mountains of southwestern Bulgaria begins to loosen, crocuses push through the thinning snow, signalling the arrival of spring in the country's highest mountain range. These early bloomers use stored nutrients to quickly grow in cold conditions, completing much of their life cycle before taller plants emerge. Their clustered blossoms unfurl over alpine meadows in sweeping purple ribbons, creating a striking contrast with bright snowfields and crisp morning light.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.RilaCrocuses_ROW4635215657_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.RilaCrocuses_ROW4635215657_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Purple crocus flowers, Seven Rila Lakes, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Maya Karkalicheva/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260304_RilaCrocuses\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Seven+Rila+Lakes+Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260304_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260304_RilaCrocuses"},"Ssd":"20260304","Name":"RilaCrocuses","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4635215657","FullDateString":"4. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Our well-being is deeply connected to the natural world. Medicinal and aromatic plants (MAPs)—species used in traditional healing, modern medicine, cosmetics and food—play a vital role in daily life across the globe. An estimated 50,000 to 70,000 MAP species are harvested worldwide, with 70–95% of people in many developing countries relying on them for primary health care. Yet many of these plants face growing threats from habitat loss, overharvesting and illegal trade, making sustainable use essential for their future.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BabyElephant_ROW4423597871_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BabyElephant_ROW4423597871_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"African elephant calf playing with its mother, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Denis-Huot/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260303_BabyElephant\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260303_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260303_BabyElephant"},"Ssd":"20260303","Name":"BabyElephant","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4423597871","FullDateString":"3. Mar rrrr"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Do not be fooled by how simple Ko Samui's longtail boats look from a distance; decades of local ingenuity have shaped their slender frames. These vessels, known in Thailand as 'ruea hang yao,' emerged in the early 20th century, when fishermen repurposed vehicle engines to navigate shallow waters that larger boats couldn't reach. Handcrafted plank by plank, each boat reflects generations of skill. Their hulls burst with bold, striking colours, while decorative cloth and flowers often crown the bows—Buddhist blessings meant to safeguard both the boat and its crew.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SamuiThailand_ROW4256574976_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SamuiThailand_ROW4256574976_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Harbour and longtail boats at Ko Samui, Thailand","Copyright":"© Foto2rich/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260302_SamuiThailand\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Ko+Samui+Thailand&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260302_0800\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260302_SamuiThailand"},"Ssd":"20260302","Name":"SamuiThailand","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4256574976","FullDateString":"2. Mar rrrr"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Obrázek dne","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Další informace","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Přispět nyní","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Stručné skutečnosti:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Nedávné obrázky na domovské stránce","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Obrázek úvodní stránky pro den {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Tento den v minulosti","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Tento den v {0} {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Sdílet dnešní domovskou stránku Bingu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Stáhněte si tento obrázek. Můžete ho ale použít jenom jako tapetu.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Stáhnout tento obrázek","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"Tento obrázek není dostupný ke stažení jako tapeta.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"In